{"id":12553,"date":"2022-10-24T19:14:46","date_gmt":"2022-10-24T19:14:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=12553"},"modified":"2022-10-24T19:14:49","modified_gmt":"2022-10-24T19:14:49","slug":"the-pandemic-is-over-disability-twitter-responds-to-president-biden","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/the-pandemic-is-over-disability-twitter-responds-to-president-biden\/","title":{"rendered":"&#8220;The Pandemic is Over&#8221;? Disability Twitter Responds to President Biden"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-1 wp-block-column\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">All Biden&#39;s words have done is make clear&#8211;abundantly clear&#8211;what we already have known: that we are on our own for the pandemic and the little that still remain (for some), will be gone soon (obvi wealthy folks will be able access whatever they want whenever as per usual).<\/p>&mdash; Mia Mingus (@miamingus) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/miamingus\/status\/1572017374018277377?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">September 20, 2022<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-column\">\n<p>The September 18, 2022 episode of 60 Minutes showed President Biden remarking <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=MIQz0fsX38U\">&#8220;the pandemic is over&#8221;<\/a> at an auto show in Detroit. &#8220;No one\u2019s wearing masks. Everybody seems to be in pretty good shape.&#8221; Disability activists on Twitter immediately responded. The following day, <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/miamingus\/status\/1572017374018277377\" target=\"_bl